    "body": "### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.9.0-dev-379+g38863f524\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A, vim doesn't have laststatus=3\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nWindows 11\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nWindows Terminal 1.15.2874.0\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nN/A\n\n### Installation\n\nRepo\n\n### How to reproduce the issue\n\n```vim\r\n\" minimal.vim\r\nset laststatus=3\r\n:au BufEnter,BufWinEnter *.c,*.h echo 'Entering a C or C++ file'\r\n```\r\n\r\n```c\r\n// Minimal C file\r\n```\r\n\r\nRecreate with `nvim --clean -u minimal.vim minimal.c`\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n\"Entering a C or C++ file\" to show up in the message box.\n\n### Actual behavior\n\nNothing shows up, and nothing is stored in the message history.",
